# VPS and production deployment

The user **does not have VPS access** at this time. Treat production/VPS as off-limits by default.

## Never do unless the user explicitly asks

- SSH into the VPS (e.g. `ssh myvps`, `ssh root@…`)
- Run deploy or VPS scripts: `npm run vps:deploy`, `tools/deploy-alphabridge-vps.sh`, `tools/migrate-hostinger.sh`, `tools/vps-fix-alphabridge.sh`, `tools/pull-production-db.sh`, etc.
- Push, rsync, scp, or copy code or builds to the VPS or production server
- Run remote commands on production (PM2 restart, nginx reload, `npm run db:migrate` on VPS, etc.)
- Git push to a production/deploy remote if that would update the live server

## Allowed without asking

- Local development: `npm run dev`, `npm run dev:api`, local `npm run db:migrate`, local Docker MySQL
- Edit deploy scripts and docs in the repo (do not execute them on VPS)
- Explain deployment steps for the user to run manually later

## When the user explicitly requests VPS work

Only then may you SSH, deploy, or push to production — and only what they asked for (nothing extra).

If deployment is needed but they did not ask to touch the VPS, give **local-only** steps or written instructions instead of running remote commands.
